## remoteConfig.RemoteConfig.rollback() method

Rolls back a project's published Remote Config template to the specified version. A rollback is equivalent to getting a previously published Remote Config template and re-publishing it using a force update.

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
rollback(versionNumber: string | number): Promise<RemoteConfigTemplate>;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  versionNumber | string \| number | The version number of the Remote Config template to roll back to. The specified version number must be lower than the current version number, and not have been deleted due to staleness. Only the last 300 versions are stored. All versions that correspond to non-active Remote Config templates (that is, all except the template that is being fetched by clients) are also deleted if they are more than 90 days old.  A promise that fulfills with the published <code>RemoteConfigTemplate</code>. |

<b>Returns:</b>

Promise&lt;[RemoteConfigTemplate](./firebase-admin.remoteconfig.remoteconfigtemplate.md)<!-- -->&gt;
